{"parse":{"title":"Wreck (2)/es","pageid":3036,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><big><big><big>Naufragio</big></big></big>\n</p><p><br>\nNaufragio, tras un siniestro mar\u00edtimo, significa:\n</p>\n<ol><li>a)\tun barco hundido o varado; o</li>\n<li>b)\tcualquier parte de un barco hundido o varado, incluido cualquier objeto que est\u00e9 o haya estado a bordo de dicho barco; o</li>\n<li>c)\tcualquier objeto perdido en el mar por un barco y que est\u00e9 varado, hundido o a la deriva en el mar; o</li>\n<li>d)\tun barco que est\u00e9 a punto, o pueda esperarse razonablemente que se hunda o vare, donde todav\u00eda no se est\u00e9n tomando medidas efectivas  para ayudar al barco o cualquier propiedad en peligro.</li></ol>\n<p><br>\n</p><p>Fuente: Convenio de Nairobi 2017, proporcionado por el Comit\u00e9 <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"47f45e65244c17ec9fa8771a5c6d60e1\">ARM</span> de <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\">IALA</span> en el documento ARM7-12.1.14 en 2017.\n</p><p><br>\n<i>Esto reemplaza la definici\u00f3n n\u00famero 1-2-205 en la edici\u00f3n original del Diccionario <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\">IALA</span> (1970-1989).</i>\n</p>\n<div class=\"LanguageLinks\">\n<table width=\"100%\">\n<tbody><tr valign=\"top\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF\">\n<td style=\"width: 25px; padding-left: 0em; border-right: 1px solid #aaaaaa;border-left: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-top: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-bottom: 1px solid #EEF3E2;\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:25px-Geographylogo.png\" class=\"mw-file-description\" title=\"Languages\"><img alt=\"Languages\" src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/8/82/25px-Geographylogo.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" class=\"mw-file-element\"></a></span></td>\n<td style=\"padding: 1px 1em 0; background: #EEF3E2;\">\n<p><b><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/Wreck_(2)\" title=\"Wreck (2)\">English</a></b>\n<span></span>\n\u00a0\u2022\u00a0<span lang=\"fr\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/Wreck_(2)/fr\" title=\"Wreck (2)/fr\">fran\u00e7ais</a></span>\n\u00a0\u2022\u00a0<span lang=\"es\"><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">espa\u00f1ol</a></span>\n<span></span>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"47f45e65244c17ec9fa8771a5c6d60e1\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Aids to Navigation Requirements and Management Committee (IALA)\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - AISM\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260615164141\nCache expiry: 86400\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: []\nCPU time usage: 0.034 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.043 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 76/1000000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 1017/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 173/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/100\nExpensive parser function count: 3/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   11.518      1 Template:Languages\n100.00%   11.518      1 -total\n 63.38%    7.300      4 Template:Languages/Lang\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wiki_iala_dictionary_1_41:pcache:idhash:3036-0!canonical and timestamp 20260615164141 and revision id 8530. Rendering was triggered because: page-view\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","*":"1.2_Navigation"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Indice_alfabeto_Espa\u00f1ol"},{"sortkey":"","*":"IALA_Dictionary_2018_Revision"},{"so